{"id":14881799,"mediaExerciseId":"8f922512-404f-42ba-9222-615a7fe31d50","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"22","chapterTitle":"Behavioral Finance: Implications For Financial Management","groupId":612479,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":761,"solutions":[{"id":5987233,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this question, we need to recall what overconfidence is and how it can affect the decision making of traders and investors. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Overconfidence can negatively affect the firm and its shareholders because if the manager overestimates their ability to forecast the price of the market, they can be put into losses due to bad trades. \n\nAside from this, overconfidence can also cloud the manager's decision making skills so they may already know that the trades they made are bad but due to their overconfidence in the future of the stock, they will hold on to it instead of cutting the losses to a minimum. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b247ff57ac69ea55175fae483edb21e5/eb531fdc6cc753b66acac0ebb1b117f1/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/b247ff57ac69ea55175fae483edb21e5/eb531fdc6cc753b66acac0ebb1b117f1/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"0a561da8-60b9-452b-ba97-551fde9feff9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.